# Phase 3 Revision: Dedicated Bind Page

## Overview

Replace the inline `<GitHubSetupGate>` rendered inside the org layout with a dedicated `/account/teams/new/bind` page. The org layout redirects to this page instead of swapping out its own UI, making the flow a proper multi-step route rather than a layout hack.

## Current State

Phase 1 (DB schema) and Phase 2 (callback hardening) are complete and deployed. Phase 3 is partially implemented with:

- `apps/app/src/app/(app)/(org)/[slug]/_components/github-setup-gate.tsx` — inline gate component
- `apps/app/src/app/(app)/(org)/[slug]/layout.tsx:54-62` — binding check renders `<GitHubSetupGate>` inline
- `apps/app/src/lib/github-binding.ts` — server-side DB query (keep as-is)
- `api/app/src/router/org/github-binding.ts` — tRPC router (keep as-is)
- `apps/app/src/app/(app)/(user)/(pending-allowed)/account/teams/new/_components/team-name-form.tsx:39` — redirects to `/${data.slug}`

## Desired End State

After this revision:

1. **Team creation** (`team-name-form.tsx`) redirects to `/account/teams/new/bind?slug=acme-inc`
2. **Bind page** at `/account/teams/new/bind` shows "Connect your GitHub organization" UI with the connect button, error handling, and on success redirects to `/${slug}`
3. **Org layout** (`[slug]/layout.tsx`) when no active binding, does a server-side `redirect()` to `/account/teams/new/bind?slug=${slug}` instead of rendering the gate inline
4. **GitHubSetupGate component** is deleted — its logic moves into the bind page

## What We're NOT Doing

- Changing the binding check logic in layout (keep `getGitHubBinding`)
- Changing the tRPC `githubBinding.get` router
- Changing anything in Phase 1 or Phase 2
- Adding auth/access checks on the bind page beyond what the route group already provides (the `(pending-allowed)` group handles auth)

## Implementation

### Phase 1: Create bind page and update routing

#### 1. Create the bind page

**File**: `apps/app/src/app/(app)/(user)/(pending-allowed)/account/teams/new/bind/page.tsx` (new)

This is a client component that:
- Reads `slug` from `useSearchParams()`
- Shows the same UI as current `GitHubSetupGate` (heading, description, connect button, error display)
- Uses `useOAuthPopup` with `provider: "github"`
- Listens for `github_error` on `BroadcastChannel` to display binding rejection errors
- On success (`github_connected`), does `router.push(/${slug})` — the org layout re-checks the binding and renders normally
- Wraps the content with `<Suspense>` for `useSearchParams()` prerender compatibility

```tsx
"use client";

import { Icons } from "@repo/ui/components/icons";
import { useTRPC } from "@repo/app-trpc/react";
import { useRouter, useSearchParams } from "next/navigation";
import { Suspense, useCallback, useEffect, useState } from "react";
import { useOAuthPopup } from "~/hooks/use-oauth-popup";

const ERROR_MESSAGES: Record<string, string> = {
  github_org_bound_to_other:
    "This GitHub organization is already connected to another Lightfast team.",
  org_already_bound:
    "This team is already connected to a different GitHub organization.",
};

function BindContent() {
  const router = useRouter();
  const searchParams = useSearchParams();
  const slug = searchParams.get("slug");
  const trpc = useTRPC();
  const [error, setError] = useState<string | null>(null);

  // Listen for binding errors from the popup via BroadcastChannel
  useEffect(() => {
    const channel = new BroadcastChannel("oauth-connections");
    channel.onmessage = (event: MessageEvent) => {
      const data = event.data as { type?: string; reason?: string };
      if (data.type === "github_error" && data.reason) {
        setError(
          ERROR_MESSAGES[data.reason] ?? `Connection failed: ${data.reason}`
        );
      }
    };
    return () => channel.close();
  }, []);

  const { handleConnect, isConnecting } = useOAuthPopup({
    provider: "github",
    queryKeysToInvalidate: [
      trpc.githubBinding.get.queryKey(),
      trpc.connections.generic.listInstallations.queryKey(),
    ],
    onSuccess: () => {
      if (slug) {
        router.push(`/${slug}`);
      }
    },
  });

  const handleClick = useCallback(() => {
    setError(null);
    handleConnect();
  }, [handleConnect]);

  if (!slug) {
    return null;
  }

  return (
    <div className="flex flex-1 items-center justify-center px-4 pb-32">
      <div className="w-full max-w-md space-y-4">
        {/* Logo */}
        <div className="w-fit rounded-sm bg-card p-3">
          <Icons.logoShort className="h-5 w-5 text-foreground" />
        </div>

        <div className="space-y-4">
          <h1 className="pb-4 font-medium font-pp text-2xl text-foreground">
            Connect your GitHub organization
          </h1>
          <p className="text-muted-foreground">
            Lightfast requires a GitHub organization to get started. Connect
            yours to begin.
          </p>
        </div>

        {error && <p className="text-sm text-destructive">{error}</p>}

        <button
          type="button"
          onClick={handleClick}
          disabled={isConnecting}
          className="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg bg-primary px-6 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-primary-foreground hover:bg-primary/90 disabled:opacity-50"
        >
          {isConnecting ? "Connecting..." : "Connect GitHub"}
        </button>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}

export default function BindPage() {
  return (
    <Suspense>
      <BindContent />
    </Suspense>
  );
}
```

Note: The page follows the same visual pattern as the team creation page (`/account/teams/new/page.tsx`) — logo, heading, content in a centered column with `pb-32` offset. It sits within the `(pending-allowed)` route group so no additional auth logic is needed.

#### 2. Update org layout to redirect instead of rendering inline

**File**: `apps/app/src/app/(app)/(org)/[slug]/layout.tsx`

Replace the inline `<GitHubSetupGate>` render (lines 54-62) with a `redirect()` call:

```typescript
// Before (lines 54-62):
const binding = await getGitHubBinding(org.id);
if (!binding || binding.status !== "active") {
  return (
    <HydrateClient>
      <GitHubSetupGate orgSlug={slug} />
    </HydrateClient>
  );
}

// After:
const binding = await getGitHubBinding(org.id);
if (!binding || binding.status !== "active") {
  redirect(`/account/teams/new/bind?slug=${slug}`);
}
```

Also:
- Add `import { redirect } from "next/navigation";` (already has `notFound` from there)
- Remove `import { GitHubSetupGate } from "./_components/github-setup-gate";`
- Remove `import { HydrateClient } from "@repo/app-trpc/server";` only if it's no longer used — but it IS used on line 64 for the normal render path, so keep it.

